HEADWORD: Carpal
<hw>Car"pal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Carpus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
carpus, or wrist.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the bones or
cartilages of the carpus; a carpale.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Carpal angle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the angle
at the last joint of the folded wing of a bird.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carpale</ent>⟦br⟧
